can we use `IObuff` or `NameBuff` instead of allocating? Will need to truncate if the string is bigger than IOSIZE, but that doesn't seem likely here.

sth like this (untested):

```suggestion
    size_t length = MIN(strlen(name), 100) + sizeof("Vimscript function \"\"") + 1;
    vim_snprintf(IObuff, length, "Vimscript function \"%s\"", name);
    int ret = luaL_error(lstate, e_fast_api_disabled, IObuff);
```

